					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Other options:<br />- Don't hold total bytes of saves larger than you can keep in WRAM (There's nothing that says you have to use the entirety of the 4 KiB sector size.)<br />- Use two sectors, and swap which one holds the save back and forth.<br /><br />Because of how flash works (converting bits from 1 to 0 can be done in any order at any time; converting bits back to 1 can only be done 32 kibit at a time) there may be more cleverness that takes advantage of this.</div>

